**a.)** For this question, we will solve for the expected rate of return. This can be done by first solving for the net income of the company. To do this, we will use this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Net income}&=\text{EBIT}-(\text{All-equity stock}-\text{Company stock}) \times \text{Debt rate}
\end{aligned}$$

Substituting the values, we will get a net income of:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Net income}&=\$73,000-(\$720,000-\$360,000) \times 0.07\\[15 pt]
&=\$47,800
\end{aligned}$$

The net income for this company is $\$47,800$
